PROJECT RECAP
Teaching Notes: Personal Notes App with Auth
*Project Recap Starting Today*

*Goal:*
Build a web application where users can sign up, log in, and manage their personal notes. Each user can only see and manage their own notes.

Key Concepts Students Learn:
1. Node.js & Express fundamentals
2. EJS templating for dynamic pages
3. CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
4. MongoDB for persistent storage
5. Authentication & Authorization using express-session
6. Password hashing with bcrypt
7. Basic CSS styling for clean UI


Step 1
Setting up the folder structure and initializing the project with npm.

Step 2
Installing necessary packages: express, ejs, mongoose, express-session (stores user sessions for authentication), bcrypt, body-parser, connect-mongo (store session data in Mongodb for persistence) dotenv method-override, nodemon.

Step 3
We define the .env file to store environment variables like PORT, MONGODB_URI, and SESSION_SECRET.

Step 4
Database connection using Mongoose to connect to MongoDB in db.js file inside config folder.